    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Logging records structured events during agent execution — run start, tool invocations, LLM latency, errors — so operators can search, alert, and reconstruct sessions. Good logging turns opaque agent loops into auditable timelines without logging secrets or full prompts at info level in production."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What it is"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Python "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "logging",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " module emits leveled messages (DEBUG, INFO, WARNING, ERROR). Structured logging encodes fields as JSON (via "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "structlog",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " or JSON formatter) for ingestion into ELK, Datadog, or CloudWatch. Each log line should carry "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "run_id",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "session_id",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", and component name."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import logging\nimport structlog\n\nstructlog.configure(\n    processors=[\n        structlog.processors.add_log_level,\n        structlog.processors.TimeStamper(fmt=\"iso\"),\n        structlog.processors.JSONRenderer(),\n    ]\n)\nlog = structlog.get_logger()\n\nasync def invoke_tool(run_id: str, tool: str, args: dict) -> dict:\n    log.info(\"tool_start\", run_id=run_id, tool=tool, arg_keys=list(args.keys()))\n    try:\n        result = await _execute(tool, args)\n        log.info(\"tool_done\", run_id=run_id, tool=tool, duration_ms=...)\n        return result\n    except Exception:\n        log.exception(\"tool_failed\", run_id=run_id, tool=tool)\n        raise"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why it matters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When an agent deletes the wrong file or loops 50 times, logs with run_id show exact tool sequence and timestamps. Support teams search \"run_id:abc tool:delete_file\" instead of reading raw stdout. Compliance may require audit logs of autonomous actions."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Benefits"
